        "title": "AWS Lambda Serverless",
        "content": "### AWS Lambda Serverless\n\n**AWS Lambda** runs your code without managing servers. You upload functions that execute in response to events, paying only for actual execution time - perfect for event-driven applications and microservices.\n\n#### How Lambda Works\n\n**Function Execution Model**:\n1. Event triggers function (API call, file upload, scheduled time)\n2. AWS provisions compute resources automatically\n3. Your code executes (maximum 15 minutes)\n4. Resources are released, billing stops\n\n**Supported Languages**: Python, Node.js, Java, C#, Go, Ruby, PowerShell\n\n#### Common Triggers\n\n**API Gateway**: HTTP requests trigger functions\n```python\nimport json\n\ndef lambda_handler(event, context):\n    # Process API request\n    name = event['queryStringParameters']['name']\n    return {\n        'statusCode': 200,\n        'body': json.dumps(f'Hello {name}!')\n    }\n```\n\n**S3 Events**: Process files when uploaded\n```python\ndef lambda_handler(event, context):\n    # Triggered when file uploaded to S3\n    bucket = event['Records'][0]['s3']['bucket']['name']\n    key = event['Records'][0]['s3']['object']['key']\n    \n    # Process image, generate thumbnail\n    print(f'Processing {key} from {bucket}')\n```\n\n**CloudWatch Events**: Scheduled execution\n- Run daily reports at 6 AM\n- Clean up temporary files hourly\n- Send weekly summary emails\n\n#### Practical Examples\n\n**Image Processing Pipeline**:\n1. User uploads photo to S3 bucket\n2. S3 triggers Lambda function\n3. Lambda resizes image, creates thumbnail\n4. Processed images stored back in S3\n\n**API Backend**:\n```python\n# Simple user registration API\ndef register_user(event, context):\n    user_data = json.loads(event['body'])\n    \n    # Validate email\n    # Store in database\n    # Send welcome email\n    \n    return {\n        'statusCode': 201,\n        'body': json.dumps({'message': 'User registered successfully'})\n    }\n```\n\nüí° **Cost Benefits**: A function running 100ms, 1000 times daily costs ~$0.0002/day vs. ~$26/month for smallest EC2 instance.\n\nüîß **Integration**: Lambda functions can read from S3 buckets, write to databases, and respond to API calls - creating serverless architectures that scale automatically.\n\n‚ö†Ô∏è **Limitations**: 15-minute maximum execution, cold start delays, stateless execution model."
