        "title": "Amazon VPC Networking",
        "content": "### Amazon VPC Networking\n\n**Amazon Virtual Private Cloud (VPC)** creates isolated network environments in AWS, giving you complete control over virtual networking including IP addresses, subnets, and security policies.\n\n#### VPC Fundamentals\n\n**Private Network Space**: Your VPC uses private IP ranges:\n- `10.0.0.0/16` (65,536 IP addresses)\n- `172.16.0.0/16` (65,536 IP addresses)  \n- `192.168.0.0/16` (65,536 IP addresses)\n\nüéì **Example**: A company VPC using `10.0.0.0/16` can host thousands of resources with private communication.\n\n#### Subnets Organization\n\n**Public Subnets**: Resources accessible from internet\n- Web servers, load balancers\n- `10.0.1.0/24` (256 IP addresses)\n- Connected to Internet Gateway\n\n**Private Subnets**: Internal resources only\n- Databases, application servers\n- `10.0.2.0/24` (256 IP addresses)\n- Access internet via NAT Gateway\n\n```\nVPC (10.0.0.0/16)\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Public Subnet (10.0.1.0/24)\n‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Web Server EC2\n‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Private Subnet (10.0.2.0/24)\n    ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Database EC2\n```\n\n#### Security Groups\n\n**Virtual Firewalls** controlling traffic to instances:\n\n| Direction | Protocol | Port | Source | Purpose |\n|-----------|----------|------|--------|---------|\n| Inbound | HTTP | 80 | 0.0.0.0/0 | Web traffic |\n| Inbound | SSH | 22 | Your IP | Admin access |\n| Outbound | All | All | 0.0.0.0/0 | Allow responses |\n\n#### Practical Architecture\n\n**Three-Tier Web Application**:\n\n1. **Web Tier** (Public Subnet):\n   - EC2 instances running web servers\n   - Security group allows HTTP/HTTPS from anywhere\n   - Elastic Load Balancer distributes traffic\n\n2. **Application Tier** (Private Subnet):\n   - EC2 instances running business logic\n   - Security group allows traffic only from web tier\n   - Lambda functions for serverless processing\n\n3. **Database Tier** (Private Subnet):\n   - RDS database instances\n   - Security group allows traffic only from app tier\n   - S3 for file storage and backups\n\nüí° **Security Benefits**: Database servers never directly accessible from internet, reducing attack surface.\n\n‚úÖ **Best Practices**:\n- Use multiple Availability Zones for high availability\n- Implement least-privilege security group rules\n- Separate environments with different VPCs\n- Use VPC Flow Logs for network monitoring\n\nüîß **Real Example**: E-commerce site with web servers in public subnets serving customers, application servers in private subnets processing orders, and databases in isolated private subnets storing sensitive customer data."
